6th North-South Red Cross Talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mt. Kumgang Resort, August 25 (KCNA) -- The 6th North-South Red Cross Talks were held at Mt. Kumgang resort from August 23 to 25.
 Present there were members of the delegation of the north side headed by Choe Song Ik, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the Red Cross Society of the DPRK, and members of the delegation of the south side with Jang Sok Jun, secretary general of the south Korean Red Cross, as chief delegate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides issued a joint press release at the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to it, at the talks the north and the south were close to a consensus of views on a series of issues and agreed to pursue further discussion on some issues in the days ahead.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's Work Held in India 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 26 (KCNA) -- A seminar on leader  Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Exalt the Brilliance of Comrade Kim Il Sung's Idea on the Youth Movement and the Achievements Made under His Leadership" was held by the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung on Aug. 20 on the occasion of the Day of Youth.
 Balzor Singh Chauhan, chairman of the group, said at the seminar that the idea of the youth movement and the politics of attaching importance to the youth clarified and maintained by President Kim Il Sung reflect the character of the era of independence and precious experience gained in the revolutionary education and training of young people at each stage of developing revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il regarded the issue of youth as an essential one related to the destiny of the country and the nation and the future of the revolution and set out the original idea and theory on the youth movement and worked heart and soul for its growth and development, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il comprehensively indicated tasks and ways for defending and carrying forward Kim Il Sung's idea of the youth movement and leadership exploits, he noted, expressing belief that the Korean youth led by Kim Jong Il would always stand in the van of the world progressive youth movement.

Anniversary of Korea's Liberation Celebrated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 26 (KCNA) -- Lectures, photo exhibitions, film shows and meetings were held in Peru, Austria, India, Tanzania, Thailand, Belarus, Yemen and Nepal from August 3 to 15 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 Luis Mateo Munoz, general secretary of the Socialist Party of Peru, in a lecture said that the world progressive people remember with deep emotion the undying feats performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu on behalf of the Korean people and humankind. The 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation marks a significant occasion of demonstrating to the world that the DPRK is, indeed, a powerful country which remains shining along with the august names of the three great persons of Mt. Paektu, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Helmut Heidweger, chief of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Kim Il Sung-Kim Jong Il in Vienna, in a lecture said that the Korean nation would surely accomplish the cause of reunification before long as it is led by Kim Jong Il.
 B. C. Gupta, chairman of the Juche Idea Study Society of Delhi, in a lecture said that the undying feats President Kim Il Sung performed by liberating Korea would shine long with the Songun era thanks to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Banou Keita, director general of the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea, addressing a meeting, praised Kim Il Sung as the benefactor of Korea's liberation and the great sun of new Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film shows watched "The Fatherly Leader with Anti-Japanese Revolutionary Fighters", "The Respected Comrade Kim Jong Il Is the Great Thinker and Theoretician" and other Korean films. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the lecture in Austria.
 Meanwhile, seminars on the feats Kim Il Sung performed by liberating Korea were held in Syria, Romania and Uganda on August 1

Russian Beryozka Dancing Troupe Performs in Wonsan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Wonsan, August 25 (KCNA) -- The visiting Russian Beryozka Dancing Troupe gave performances in Wonsan on August 24 and 25.
 It put on the stage colorful and peculiar numbers in Wonsan in the wake of its successful performances in Pyongyang and Hamhung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance began with a chorus "Song of General Kim Jong Il." The audience were deeply impressed when the Russian artistes truthfully represented with rich volumes Korean songs "Song Dedicated to Comrade Kim Jong Il," "The General of Korea" and "Recalling the Old Home," expressing profound reverence for the generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their women's group dance "Beryozka," a typical number of the dancing troupe, women's group dances "River Volga" and "Girls", men's group dances "Carters" and "Song of Labor," a mixed group dance "Holiday Dance" and other numbers the artistes impressively represented the traditional customs and industrious work style and national sentiments of the Russians. In a trio dance "Witticism Dance" and a mixed group dance "Petrushka" they successfully dealt with the humorous theme of the works to the laughter of the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their presentation deeply impressed the audience as it was a good combination of graceful dance pieces high in artistry dealing with Russians' sentiments and lifestyle.

Stop to Military Exercises Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 26 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity and the People's Solidarity in south Korea reportedly called a press conference around the U.S. embassy in Seoul on August 22 at which they declared they would stage a joint struggle in demand of a stop to "Ulji Focus Lens-05" joint military exercises.
 At the conference speakers recalled that the south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command" announced its plan to stage the joint military exercises involving the U.S. forces and the south Korean army. They denounced the exercises as a war rehearsal for aggression aimed to acquire the concept of the U.S. operation for a preemptive attack on the north in case of "contingency" and complete combined arrangements for a total war.
 Then, an action program of the organizations was announced to jointly stage a vigorous struggle for a halt to the war exercises. According to it, the organizations will conduct a monthly event of joint action against the U.S. and war in front of the U.S. embassy on August 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, civic and public organizations, including the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the Solidarity for Social Progress, held a press conference in front of the building of the Defence Ministry on August 22 in demand of a stop to the U.S. forces' rehearsal for a war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release published at the conference said that the current joint military exercises, staged for the first time after the U.S. Second Division, a main pillar of the U.S. forces in south Korea, was reorganized into a future-oriented division, are aimed to increase the division's commanding and control capability and precision strike capacity.
 It strongly demanded an immediate stop to the exercises, saying that they will spoil the atmosphere of reconciliation and cooperation among Koreans grown up through the August 15 grand national festival and create military tensions and threaten peace in Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An open letter to the chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff of the south Korean army was read out at the conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the conference the organizations handed over the letter to the Defence Ministry.

Joint Military Exercises Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 26 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification reportedly published a statement titled "U.S. forces, stop at once 'Ulji Focus Lens-05' war exercises" on August 22.
 The U.S. forces, in league with the south Korean army, the statement said, have launched the "Ulji Focus Lens-05" joint military exercises in a bid to render the situation of the Korean Peninsula extremely strained and arrest reconciliation and cooperation between the north and the south at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people in the south have clearly known that the U.S. forces in south Korea are the root cause of aggravating the situation on the peninsula and threatening peace, it noted, demanding an immediate halt to the war exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils on August 21 issued a statement titled "U.S. forces, stop 'Ulji Focus Lens-05' war exercises aimed at a preemptive attack on the north and get out of this land at once."

Rodong Sinmun on General March of Songun Revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 26 (KCNA) -- The general march of Songun revolution now being staged by the Korean people is a dynamic onward movement in the present times to reach the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the banner of the great Songun idea and a new mass movement at a higher stage which has successfully carried forward the proud history and tradition of the revolutionary grand march.
 Rodong Sinmun Friday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: The general march of Songun revolution is a dynamic onward movement making successful progress thanks to the concerted efforts of the army and the people of the DPRK united close around leader Kim Jong Il.
 The army and the people of the DPRK absolutely trust and follow their leader and uphold the idea and intention of the Workers' Party of Korea with loyalty all the time under the uplifted slogan "Once the Party determines, we will move!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general march of Songun revolution is one based on confidence as it is making progress, guided by the revolutionary faith of the army and the people in socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They deeply grasped through their life experience the revolutionary truth that defending socialism means victory but abandoning it means death. 
 The above-said march represents a sacred struggle to firmly defend man-centered Korean style socialism from the moves of the imperialists to isolate and stifle it and add shine to it. The Korean people's faith in socialism has become a scientific outlook on the world and they regard socialism as the most precious life and soul and a genuine life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The key to victory in the general march of Songun revolution lies in energetically pushing forward the revolution and construction with firm faith in socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This march means a powerful mass onward movement which makes progress on the basis of the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance and by its force.
 It is the steadfast stand of the Party to build a rich and powerful country on its own, trusting its people and it is also the fixed will of the army and the people of the DPRK.

Performance of "Arirang" Goes On
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 26 (KCNA) -- The grand mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang", prepared to celebrate the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of Korea, has been given before full audience at May Day Stadium in Pyongyang.
  "Arirang", created in Juche 91 (2002), has been re-depicted on a higher ideological and artistic level. It shows that the Korean people, who once sang the song "Arirang" in tears, are  now fully demonstrating their dignity, singing the song "Arirang for Prosperity". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The creators, basing themselves on the original work, have embossed the first scene of the second act "Ye, Bright Moon over My Country" and  various other acts and scenes with eight scenic views in the Songun era and thus enriched its theme. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have portrayed well the fantastic sunrise over Mt. Paektu in a way of formative arts in the prelude and newly created the first scene of the third act "Ullim Falls", which shows fairies flying down to settle in this land, fascinated by the eight scenic views in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The high sports technique including a movement of turning round tassels with long strings on the top of three storied human pyramids in the fourth scene of the second act " Our Thriving Country", elegant and refined dancing rhythm and ever-changing formations further raise the artistic level of the performance.
 The background has been supplemented with more than 30 pictures and letters including "May Kim Il Sung's Korea shine for all ages!" and "Long live General Kim Jong Il, a peerless patriot!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each scene has been further beautified by the harmony between the background and performers, backed by electric and illumination devices, and large slide projectors and combination of flags with folding screens.
 The presentation of "Arirang", a  Kim Il Sung Prize laureate and treasure of the nation, fully shows the firm will of the Korean people, who constructed a strong country, independent, self-supporting and self-reliant in national defence under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, to build a great prosperous powerful nation without fail under the Songun leadership of the WPK.
